The paper deals with facial expression recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the issue of fine-tuning CNNs for cross-dataset scenarios, which falls under the domain adaptation subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different strategies for fine-tuning CNNs, which involves analyzing experimental results and comparing different approaches, indicating a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) subfields.
